In 1967 the club were fined 1000 pounds after an attack on referee Norman  Burtenshaw by spectators.
Aleven years later Millwall were fined 1500 pounds and had their ground  closed for two weeks after crowd trouble at an FA Cup sixth-round tie against  Ipswich. The club were also barred from staging home FA Cup ties for two  seasons.
In 1985 Millwall were fined 7,500 pounds and the following season's FA Cup  ties were made all-ticket after their fans rioted at Luton.
